              <tr> 
                <td class="chblue"><font class="h1font"> Advanced Decks</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3"><tr><td><font class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font class="h1font">Hyren Deck... &#39;Nuff said</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size=1>(3.80)</font> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=22108">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=9925">Jon "Kag" Newton</A></FONT> <font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=9925&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> ...I said, &quot;&#39;Nuff said&quot;!</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> March 13, 2002</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> / Magi - 3 <br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(822)">Yerthe</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(820)">Marella</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(665)">Elios</a><br>
<br>
/ Dream Creatures - 20 <br>
3x <a href="javascript:card_browser(467)">Cave Hyren</a><br>
3x <a href="javascript:card_browser(797)">Grass Hyren</a><br>
3x <a href="javascript:card_browser(402)">Leaf Hyren</a><br>
3x <a href="javascript:card_browser(370)">Magma Hyren</a><br>
3x <a href="javascript:card_browser(784)">Monarch Hyren</a><br>
3x <a href="javascript:card_browser(621)">Reef Hyren</a><br>
2x <a href="javascript:card_browser(716)">Rock Hyren</a><br>
<br>
/ Relics - 12 <br>
3x <a href="javascript:card_browser(652)">Rayje&#39;s Belt</a><br>
3x <a href="javascript:card_browser(510)">Staff of Hyren</a><br>
3x <a href="javascript:card_browser(512)">Warrior&#39;s Boots</a><br>
2x <a href="javascript:card_browser(507)">Relic Stalker</a><br>
1x <a href="javascript:card_browser(351)">Storm Ring</a><br>
<br>
/ Spells - 12 <br>
3x <a href="javascript:card_browser(424)">Hyren&#39;s Call</a><br>
3x <a href="javascript:card_browser(355)">Shockwave</a><br>
3x <a href="javascript:card_browser(498)">Thunderquake</a><br>
3x Ummm...NO!   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Magi<br>
<br>
Yerthe - Obviously, you should know why I picked this Magi. Starts with the Staff of Hyren, and any one Hyren, usually Reef Hyren if I go first. But, if I go second, it&#39;ll likely to be a Grass Hyren or whatever, which fits the best in the situation. His energizing effect is ownage, and so on.<br>
<br>
Marella - Starts with a Grass Hyren and has a whopping energize of 8. Her effect does hurt a tad bit, but, if I&#39;m lucky, I&#39;ll have a Belt to prevent that. Or I&#39;ll have enough cards in my hand. You constantly play Hyren with her.<br>
<br>
Elios - Has an elite energize, or, if necessary, an elite card drawer. Hopefully, I&#39;ll manage to have a good hand at this point, so I&#39;ll be able to continue energizing at 8.<br>
<br>
<br>
Dream Creatures<br>
<br>
Cave Hyren - Energy manipulation. Um, I don&#39;t think I can really say anything else. Just give energy when others need it.<br>
<br>
Grass Hyren - Elite at defense. It will tick your opponent when they&#39;re attacking. A beatdown and defense Hyren, basically.<br>
<br>
Leaf Hyren - Same as Cave Hyren. Energy manipulation.<br>
<br>
Magma Hyren - This Hyren is tech. It&#39;s pretty sweet when you have at least two of those in play. Using Healing Flame on each other is fun. Can be used with Cave or Leaf Hyren.<br>
<br>
Monarch Hyren - This Hyren can be very good. If you have plenty of Hyren out in play, ooh, you&#39;re lucky. Free energy! He fetches Hyrens from the deck, too, which is useful.<br>
<br>
Reef Hyren - Ahh, disruption. If you&#39;re thinking of playing this, ALWAYS try to leave at least 3-4 energy on your Magi.<br>
<br>
Rock Hyren - Mainly used with Hyren&#39;s Call. Although, I don&#39;t see why this Creature should be hard to play with two high energizers.<br>
<br>
<br>
Relics<br>
<br>
Rayje&#39;s Belt - Duh.<br>
<br>
Staff of Hyren - Another duh.<br>
<br>
Warrior&#39;s Boots - Just need this Creature to kill off the current Magi? Easily done.<br>
<br>
Relic Stalker - Relic destruction is needed, of course.<br>
<br>
Storm Ring - Just a tech with Elios. Why even add it? It adds two energy to Hyren, not just one.<br>
<br>
<br>
Spells<br>
<br>
Hyren&#39;s Call - Usually used with Rock Hyren, or Monarch Hyren. Don&#39;t use it on the other Hyren, unless neccessary, because you&#39;re just gonna lose energy.<br>
<br>
Shockwave - Need to clear a big Creature out of your path? Done.<br>
<br>
Thunderquake - Sometimes weenies will tick you. Clear the path with this.<br>
<br>
Ummm...NO! - Prevent your big Hyrens! Just hope, at the right time, you&#39;ll have at least 4 energy on your Magi and this card. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/magination/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=22108"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=22108" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/magination/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></td></tr></table></td>
        </tr>
